- DAG-SYM-ARGTs always have an NE that can be calculated in linear time (p.506-507);
- The problem of deciding if an ARGT has an NE is ΣP2-complete (p.508-509);
- The Price of Stability and Price of Anarchy are both unbounded in general ARGTs (p.510-511);
- The Best Response problem is NP-complete for general ARGTs but solvable in linear time for DAG-SYM-ARGTs (p.511-512)

gaps:
